      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i was also reading about setbacks and property lines. what happens if a building or a structure actually encroaches a bit onto a neighboring property or a public right-of-way? like, how does the city handle those kinds of boundary violations in a residential area?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When a structure encroaches on a neighbor's property or a public right-of-way, it is a violation of property lines and zoning codes. The city typically handles this through a formal complaint process, which can lead to the issuance of a Notice of Violation. The responsible party is usually required to remedy the situation by removing the encroachment or obtaining a formal variance from the city. If the violation is ignored, the city can impose fines or issue a stop-work order.",
